t31.text: On my farm about 30% of our farm is thick scrub like this. With well managed rotational grazing and approved use of fire we are wanting to improve soils and make the landscape into a semi open grassland with shrubs. Rather than an over grown most scrub fire hazard.

t32.text: Biosolids have there place but they are not a silver bullet for soil health. I'm yet to see any trial results showing significant improvements while growing monoculture crops for human consumption.

t33.text: Ideally I think we need to subdivide paddocks and double or triple goat numbers. This should increase the grazing intensity substantially and keep the time in each paddock to a week or two max. But fencing costs time and money and good breeding does are $250-350 ea.
